Step 1: Define the Union-Find data structure class and initialize the parent array.  This step involves creating a class that will encapsulate the Union-Find functionality, including the union and find methods. We also need to initialize the parent array, which will be used to keep track of the root of each node. The parent array should be initialized with the indices of the nodes as its initial values, since each node initially has itself as its root.
